	   <tr><td colspan=2>***2 Hand Bash - This ability will allow the player to bash with any 2-handed weapon. <br><br>This is huge, imo.&nbsp;&nbsp;This would get the damage up for pallys and allow them to interupt casting like they always have with 1hs and shield.  <br><br>***Fearless - This ability makes the player permanently immune to fear spells. <br><br>Again, a great skill to have against casters with fear spells.  <br><br>***Slay Undead - This ability will turn the players crits into massive damage when fighting undead monsters. <br><br>Critical damage against undead should have been there all along but it's nice to see it.  But by the same token that critical hits are only occasional, there should be an ability that allows you some short duration super attack against undead.  For example, for 10 seconds all your hits do 4x damage against undead.<br><br>As for higher level undead, I'm surprised about this too.  There should be undead dragons, giants, etc.<br><br><br>***Act of Valor - This ability will allow the player to transfer all of their hitpoints to a target PC. <br><br>You won't see me using this often.  <br><br>***Pally Stun - This ability will allow the player to have the chance to stun NPC's with spells up to level 60. Normal resist rules apply.<br><br>A nice addition.  I've also heard that two new stun spells may be added to luclin at level 9 and 15.  These are great additions as well but anyone not familiar with how to interupt casting will probably not get much benefit from them.  Still, a super short casting time stun spell would be awesome.  Alternate between this, the level 30 stun and bash and the mob is stunned for the majority of the fight.<br><br>It seems as if Pallys are being groomed as the ultimate spell stuffers which is cool.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
