	   <a name=100611293161867></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100611293161867><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100611293161867>Thurgadin Gate Potion</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100611293161867#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=90790><span id= >bydebook</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 18th 2:48 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Everyone, do yourself a great favor. Get your pottery skill up to 127 or so (can be done in 2 hours real time for about 10pp) and combine 3 crystalline spider silks, 2 glass shards (bought from merchant), and a small brick of Velium on the pottery wheel. Then take the vial you have made and combine it with a HQ firing sheet in the oven. Go to the lady across from the Paladin Guild and say "What about Velium Vapors" and she will give you a mixing bowl. Put the vial and two small bricks of Velium in it and voila, you have a Gate Potion.&nbsp;&nbsp;The final product is lore and no drop, so you can only make one up at a time, but it is invaluable for getting out of sticky situations or when there are no porters on.  I keep a couple of extra vials in the bank that I have made up through the firing stage, so when I need another one, I just go to the lady across from the Pally Guild and get the mixing bowls. You can get the crystalline silks and velium bricks in CC or Velks, or buy some at auction in Gfay. No matter where you are, just right click on potion and Presto... back in Thurgadin.  Was by far the best two hours I have ever spent in EQ getting my pottery skill high enough that I was able to make this gate potion. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
