	   <tr><td colspan=2>Jcasentl,<br><br>I understand your frustration regarding the "Next Best Thing".&nbsp;&nbsp;Verant does seem to present a continuously moving target regarding high-end items and the latest and greatest.  There are a lot of people caught up in that "Uber Gear" game.<br><br>However, the intent of the post wasn't to expound upon the virtues of the next best thing. Instead, it was meant to point out that with expanded skills, your chances of improving your weapons and thus improving your abilities improves as well.  There's no way to get away from the fact that one's Gear is very important in the game of EQ. This becomes even more magnified the higher level you get.<br><br>Let me explain, albeit in a simplified manner. You have a group that you play with on a regular basis (whether that's a group of RL friends, a guild group or whatever).  The group is getting stronger and stronger and taking on bigger and more powerful mobs every week.  You rise up through your 20's, 30's, 40's and are now in your 50's moving ahead full speed.  You have a decent 1-hs weapon and your skill is okay, but not maxed, but your 2-hs skill is topped out because that's what you use 90% of the time.<br><br>You are finally fighting that Rare Spawn and he drops that very nice 2-hand BLUNT weapon that would really improve your abilities and thus the abilities of your group...BUT GUESS WHAT?  You can't use it because you never practiced that skill.  You are now in your 50's with a weapon skill cap of 200+ and your skill is Zero!  So, the nice weapon goes to waste and your group's abilities are lessened because of it.<br><br>It's not about the item...it's about improving your skills to be the best asset you can be, whether that is to yourself, your group, your guild, or whoemever your may group with in the game.<br><br>Just some thoughts....<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
