	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100577524051244><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100577524051244>RE: GHeal usage</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100577524051244#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=119320><span id= >Valodec</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 14th 5:00 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>When it comes to using GHeal, I find that it helps to start casting it when people are down about two bubbles.&nbsp;&nbsp;Maybe more with casters, but generally down two bubbles.  If it gets down more than that and you are supposed to be the main healer, then you are going to have a rough time of it later in the fight.    <br><br>Also, when you are playing healer, you have to be a full time cleric, which means med, heal, med, heal.  No fighting, no helping, no stunning, no nothing.  Paladins don't have the mana pool that clerics or druids or shamen do, so we can't use our mana for anything other than healing.<br><br>Personally, the last time I was in a group as the main healer was at about level 45.  I managed to keep my group healthy while we were camped outside Karnors.  but it was close.  Since then I will help out with heals but I am never called upon to be the main healer. Greater Heal takes alot of mana and provides a decent heal, but with your mana pool you can cast all of about 5 GHs before you are oom.   Don't count on GHeal making you the healer of the group.<br><br>Also, to the people who are so annoyed with the use of LoH as the sign for the laying on of hands.  Its just an abbreviation.  Don't read so much into it.  Its really the action where a Paladin will walk up and grab ahold of someone to heal them.  Its the Laying On Of Hands.   LoH for short.   If you find that frustrates you, go ask druids why they respond to requests for SoW when the correct spelling out of the spell is "Spirit of the Wolf"<br><br>Kydjarindel Falconknight<br>52nd Paladin<br>Tribunal Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
